Date: Sat, 21 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] python-depyf: handle missing git during version discovery

The release sdist does not require a git checkout to determine the package
version. Catch FileNotFoundError as well so wheel builds do not fail when git
is absent from the RPM buildroot.

---
 setup.py | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/setup.py b/setup.py
index e74f440..d30dd5a 100644
--- a/setup.py
+++ b/setup.py
@@ -11,7 +11,7 @@ def get_git_commit_id(n_digits=8) -> Optional[str]:
         # Decode bytes to string (Python 3.x)
         commit_id = commit_id.decode('utf-8')
         return commit_id[:n_digits]
-    except subprocess.CalledProcessError as e:
+    except (subprocess.CalledProcessError, FileNotFoundError) as e:
         print("Failed to get Git commit ID:", e)
         return None
 
